quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  14,25,It gives its fruit at all times by the permission of its Lord. Allah sets forth examples for mankind in order that they may remember
  14,26,The example of an evil word is that of an evil tree uprooted from the surface of the earth with no stability
  14,27,"Those who believe with the word that stands firm, Allah will keep them firm in the life of this world and Hereafter. Those who are wrongdoers, Allah will cause them to go astray. Allah does what He wills"
  14,28,"Have you not seen those who have changed the blessings of Allah into disbelief, and have caused their people to reside in the house of destruction"
  14,29,"Hell, in which they will burn, and what an evil place to settle in"
  14,30,"They set up rivals to Allah, to mislead people from His way! Say: “Enjoy (your brief life)! But certainly, your destination is the hell fire!”"
  14,31,"Say (O Muhammad) to My devotees who have believed, that they should establish prayer, and spend in charity from what We have provided them secretly and openly; before a Day comes in which there will be neither mutual bargaining nor friendship"
  14,32,"Allah is the one Who has created the heavens and the earth, sends down water (rain) from the sky, and thereby brings forth fruits as provision for you. He has made the ships to be of service to you, that they may sail through the sea by His Command; and He has made rivers to be of service to you"
  14,33,"And He has made the sun and the moon to be of service to you, both constantly pursuing their courses; and He has made the night and the day to be of service to you"